title: 21-month-old boy dies in swimming pool at Makarau, north of Auckland
text:
21-month-old boy dies in swimming pool at Makarau, north of Auckland Last updated 19:30, February 5 2017 ARHT 
A Westpac Rescue helicopter has been despatched to Makarau the drowned toddler. 
A 21-month-old boy has died after drowning in a swimming pool at a property in Makarau, northwest of Auckland. 
An Auckland Westpac Rescue Helicopter spokeswoman said emergency services performed CPR on the young boy but were unable to revive him by the time Westpac's helicopter arrived.
